01:13:06.170 --> 01:13:10.660
Samba 3 is that it allows you to have
a single place where you're serving

01:13:11.020 --> 01:13:20.380
up file systems and printing to both
Windows users and to Mac servers.

01:13:20.400 --> 01:13:26.120
And it goes beyond that in
that the MIS manager can

01:13:26.810 --> 01:13:29.170
manage a single record and

01:13:31.440 --> 01:13:36.640
and Samba 3 can become a
primary domain controller.

01:13:38.300 --> 01:13:39.840
Now, what does this mean?

01:13:39.840 --> 01:13:45.120
This means that if I have a person
in my shop who needs to access both

01:13:45.120 --> 01:13:48.600
